---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Support — StudentFlow"
  description="Get help with StudentFlow. Common questions, troubleshooting, and how to reach the developer."
>
  <article class="post">
    <a class="back" href="/">← Back to StudentFlow</a>
    <h1>Support</h1>
    <p class="date">StudentFlow is built by one person. I read every email.</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:joeymaglalang91@gmail.com">joeymaglalang91@gmail.com</a>
        with what's happening and which iPhone you're on. I usually reply within
        a day or two.
      </p>

      <h2>Common questions</h2>

      <h3>I can't sign in with Apple</h3>
      <p>
        Sign in with Apple is optional — StudentFlow works without it. If you
        want an account but it's failing, try:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Make sure you're signed into iCloud in iOS Settings.</li>
        <li>Toggle airplane mode off and on, then try again.</li>
        <li>
          If you previously hid your email with Apple's private relay and that
          relay address is now blocking us, sign out at
          <a href="/login">studentflowapp.com/login</a> and back in.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>Still stuck? Email me with the error message and I'll dig in.</p>

      <h3>How do I connect Canvas?</h3>
      <p>
        In Canvas, go to <strong>Calendar → Calendar Feed</strong> and copy the
        ICS URL. In StudentFlow, open Settings → Canvas and paste it. The URL
        stays on your device — StudentFlow fetches the feed directly from Canvas.
      </p>

      <h3>Where are the AI features?</h3>
      <p>
        Coming soon. When they ship, you'll be able to bring your own
        Claude API key — your prompts and key never touch our servers.
      </p>

      <h3>How do tips work?</h3>
      <p>
        Tips are handled by Apple through StoreKit. Coffee ($1.99), Snack
        ($4.99), and Lunch ($9.99) all do the same thing: keep StudentFlow
        going. They don't unlock features — everything in the app is already
        yours.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I delete my account?</h3>
      <p>
        To delete the identity record stored in our authentication backend,
        email <a href="mailto:joeymaglalang91@gmail.com">joeymaglalang91@gmail.com</a>
        from the address tied to your Apple ID and I'll remove it within 30 days.
        To remove the app and its on-device data, uninstall it from your iPhone.
      </p>

      <h3>Is there an iPad or Mac version?</h3>
      <p>
        Not yet. StudentFlow is iPhone-only for now so I can keep the
        experience tight on one device. iPad and Mac are on the roadmap.
      </p>

      <h3>Privacy</h3>
      <p>
        See the <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>. The short version: no
        tracking, no analytics, no ads, your study data lives on your device.
      </p>

      <h2>Bug reports &amp; feedback</h2>
      <p>
        If something's broken or you have a feature request, email
        <a href="mailto:joeymaglalang91@gmail.com">joeymaglalang91@gmail.com</a>.
        Screenshots and the iOS version (Settings → General → About) help me
        reproduce things fast.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
